.TH PUSHBULLET "1" "December 2025" "pushbullet 202208150024-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pushbullet \- Send Pushbullet notifications
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pushbullet
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,TITLE\/\fR] [\fI\,MESSAGE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pushbullet
is a script for sending notifications through the Pushbullet service. It allows sending push notifications to connected devices including phones, tablets, and browsers.
.PP
The script interfaces with the Pushbullet API to send notes, links, and files to your devices.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B pushbullet "Alert" "Server is down"
Send a notification with title and message
.TP
.B pushbullet --config
Configure Pushbullet API token
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/pushbullet/settings.conf
User configuration file for pushbullet preferences and API token
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PUSHBULLET_TOKEN
Pushbullet API access token
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
API token not configured
.TP
.B 4
Network connection failed
.SH NOTES
